  "final_answer": "## Starshield: Segment Classification and Revenue Contribution Disclosure\n\n### Glossary Definition\nThe S-1 glossary defines **Starshield** as \"a secure satellite network designed specifically for government customers and national security applications.\"\n\n### Reporting Segment\nStarshield revenue is included in the **Connectivity** segment. The Connectivity segment operates a worldwide high-speed, low-latency broadband network powered by Starlink satellites, delivering connectivity to consumer, enterprise, and government customers.\n\nWithin the Connectivity segment, Starshield revenue is reported within the **\"Enterprise & Government\"** revenue disaggregation line item. The filing states that \"Connectivity contract revenue for Starshield customers is mostly derived from fixed-price contracts related to the development of a secure satellite network designed specifically for government and national security applications.\"\n\n### Revenue Contribution Disclosure\n**No specific revenue contribution disclosure is provided for Starshield.** The S-1 does not break out Starshield revenue as a separate dollar amount or percentage. Instead:\n\n- Starshield revenue is **aggregated** within the Connectivity segment's \"Enterprise & Government\" line item, which also includes Starlink Mobile service offerings.\n- The disaggregation table footnote only clarifies that \"Enterprise & Government revenue includes revenue from Starlink Mobile service offerings,\" with no separate mention of Starshield.\n- The filing does not state whether Starshield revenue is material to the company's overall financials.\n\n### Additional Starshield Disclosures (Accounting Treatment Only)\nWhile no revenue contribution is disclosed, the S-1 does provide accounting-policy disclosures for Starshield:\n- Starshield revenue is recognized **over time** for certain multi-year contracts using the **cost-to-cost input method**.\n- Starshield contracts are described as complex, requiring significant management judgment to estimate total costs (labor hours, shared costs, satellite material costs, expected technological changes).\n- Deferred revenue as of December 31, 2025 ($12,116 million total) primarily relates to Space agreements and Connectivity enterprise and government contracts (which includes Starshield).\n\n### Conclusion\nStarshield is classified within the **Connectivity** segment (specifically the \"Enterprise & Government\" revenue line), but the S-1 provides **no standalone revenue contribution disclosure** for Starshield. Its financial performance is aggregated with other enterprise and government connectivity contracts rather than being broken out separately.\n\n{\n  \"sources\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm\",\n      \"name\": \"SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement (filed May 20, 2026)\"\n    }\n  ]\n}",
